1 B. Any county may levy a lodging tax, not to exceed three
2 percent (3%), upon the gross proceeds or gross receipts derived from
3 the service of furnishing of rooms by hotel, apartment hotel, or
4 motel and for the furnishing of any other facility for public
5 lodging, except campsites, for the purpose of building and
6 maintaining county-owned facilities that promote tourism. Before
7 such a tax may be levied by the county, the imposition of the tax
8 shall first be approved by sixty percent (60%) of the registered
9 voters of the county voting thereon at a special election called by
10 the board of county commissioners or by initiative petition signed
11 by not less than five percent (5%) of the registered voters of the
12 county who were registered at the time of the last general election.
13 However, if sixty percent (60%) of the registered voters of a county
14 voting fail to approve such a tax, the board of county commissioners
15 shall not call another special election for such purpose for six (6)
16 months. Any tax levied or any change in the rate of a tax levied
17 pursuant to the provisions of this section shall become effective on
18 the first day of the calendar quarter following approval by the
19 voters of the county unless another effective date, which shall also
20 be on the first day of a calendar quarter, is specified in the
21 ordinance or resolution levying the tax or changing the rate of tax.
22 C. Any tax which may be levied by a county pursuant to the
23 provisions of this section shall be inapplicable to the furnishing
