13 county shall identify the duration of the tax when it is presented
14 to the voters pursuant to the provisions of subsection A or
15 subsection B of this section.
16 E. F. There are hereby created one or more county lodging tax
17 revolving funds in each county which levies a tax pursuant to the
18 provisions of this section if any or all of the proceeds of such tax
19 are not to be deposited in the general revenue fund of the county.
20 Each such revolving fund shall be designated for a particular
21 purpose and shall consist of all monies generated by such tax which
22 are designated for such purpose. Monies in such funds shall only be
23 expended for the purposes specifically designated as required by
